Do yourself a favor and stay away from this bar. When ordering a drink I gave the bartender my credit card and said to keep an open tab. I never left the bar area and attempted to order a second drink when I was told I did not have a tab open. The bartender lost my credit card and when I expressed my frustration I was told told it is only a credit card and the bartender walked away. I then stepped outside of the bar to call and cancel my lost credit card and then attempted to re enter the bar to get my friends, but was told I could not come in unless I paid a new $10 cover even after explaining my situation that I had only stepped out to cancel the credit card they lost. Not to mention both bouncers watched me walk out of the bar to make a phone call as well. Completely trashy place. If you don’t want your credit car stolen or want to pay $10 to look for it do not come here.
